.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DATASOURCE 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.7.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-datasource \- datasource catalog, export, import, diff, browse, and mutation workflows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util datasource [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B grafana-util ds [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
grafana\-util datasource is the namespace for catalog lookup, live browsing, export/import, diff, and live create/modify/delete workflows. The same namespace is also available as grafana\-util ds.
.PP
Use this namespace when you want to inspect supported datasource types, browse live inventory, export a datasource bundle, compare a local bundle with Grafana, or create and maintain live datasources.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B types
Show the built\-in supported datasource type catalog.
.TP
.B list
List live Grafana datasource inventory.
.TP
.B browse
Open a live datasource browser against Grafana with in\-place modify and delete actions.
.TP
.B inspect\-export
Inspect a local masked recovery bundle without connecting to Grafana.
.TP
.B export
Export live Grafana datasource inventory as normalized JSON plus provisioning files.
.TP
.B import
Import datasource inventory through the Grafana API.
.TP
.B diff
Compare datasource inventory from a local bundle against live Grafana and print an operator\-summary diff report.
.TP
.B add
Create one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API.
.TP
.B modify
Modify one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API.
.TP
.B delete
Delete one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-url
Grafana base URL.
.TP
.B \-\-token, \-\-basic\-user, \-\-basic\-password
shared live Grafana credentials.
.TP
.B \-\-profile
load repo\-local defaults from grafana\-util.yaml.
.TP
.B \-\-color
control JSON color output for the namespace.
.SH WORKFLOW NOTES
.PP
Datasource export follows a masked recovery contract. Treat the canonical export JSON as the replay source. Treat provisioning output as a derived projection for Grafana provisioning workflows.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
grafana-util datasource --help
.EE
.EX
grafana-util datasource types
.EE
.EX
grafana-util datasource browse --profile prod
.EE
.EX
grafana-util datasource browse --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin
.EE
.EX
grafana-util datasource types --output-format yaml
.EE
.EX
grafana-util datasource list --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --output-format text
.EE
